  <Placemark><name>1. La Casa de la Marquesa</name>
    <description>Home base · $180-260/nt
1756 mansion, two emperors slept here. Crib + courtyard suite requested.
C. Francisco I. Madero 41, Centro, 76000 Santiago de Querétaro, Qro., Mexico</description><styleUrl>#g_home</styleUrl>
    <Point><coordinates>-100.3934422,20.5918922,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
  <Placemark><name>2. Tikua Sur-Este</name>
    <description>Dinner · 6-8 PM (reserve) · $40-70
Best kitchen in the city — mole negro by candlelight.
C. Ignacio Allende Sur 13, Centro, 76000 Santiago de Querétaro, Qro., Mexico</description><styleUrl>#g_eat</styleUrl>
    <Point><coordinates>-100.39323270000001,20.591013099999998,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
  <Placemark><name>3. Mercado de la Cruz</name>
    <description>Morning · 9-10:30 AM · $10-18 cash
Carnitas + fresh juice where Querétaro actually eats.
Mercado Josefa Ortiz de Dominguez &quot;La Cruz&quot; (sobre, C/ 15 de Mayo, Centro, 76020 Santiago de Querétaro, Qro., Mexico</description><styleUrl>#g_eat</styleUrl>
    <Point><coordinates>-100.38583609999999,20.5981222,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
  <Placemark><name>4. Hank&#x27;s New Orleans Café</name>
    <description>Dinner · 6:30-8:30 PM · $45-75
Gumbo + chargrilled oysters; baby-proof noise floor.
